    • Method Detail

      • enqueue

        void enqueue(E e)
        Mutator method to add to the tail of the queue. Precondition: A valid Queue object exists and an element is passed. Postcondition: Element is inserted to the tail of the queue.
        Parameters:
        e - Element which is needed to be inserted.

      • dequeue

        E dequeue()
        Mutator method to remove from the head of the queue. Precondition: A valid Queue object exists. Postcondition: It removes from the head of the queue and return the element.
        Returns:
        Element removed from the head of the queue.

      • peek

        E peek()
        Accessor method to look at the element at the head of the queue. Precondition: A valid Queue object exists. Postcondition: It returns the element at the head of the queue.
        Returns:
        Element at the head of the queue.

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        Accessor method to check if the queue is empty. Precondition: A valid Queue object exists. Postcondition: It returns true if the queue is empty otherwise it returns False.
        Returns:
        True if stack has nothing in it.

      • isFull

        boolean isFull()
        Accessor method to only if queue is of static capacity. Precondition: A valid Queue object exists. Postcondition: It returns true if queue is of static capacity otherwise it returns False.
        Returns:
        True if queue is of static capacity.

      • dequeueAll

        void dequeueAll()
        Mutator method to clear all elements from the queue. Precondition: A valid Queue object exists. Postcondition: Queue is empty.

      • equals

        boolean equals(QueueADT<E> that)
        Accessor method to check if two queues contain equal items appearing in the same order. Precondition: A valid Queue object exists and a queue is passed. Postcondition: It returns true if two queues contain equal items appearing in the same order otherwise it returns False.
        Parameters:
        that - Queue which is needed to be compared.
        Returns:
        True if two queues contain equal items appearing in the same order.

      • toArray

        java.lang.Object[] toArray()

        Returns:
        Array containing all of the items in this queue.

      • toArray

        E[] toArray(E[] copy)
        Returns an array containing all of the elements in this list in proper sequence. The runtime type of the returned array is that of the specified array. Precondition: A valid Queue object exists and an array is passed. Postcondition: It returns an array containing all of the elements in this list in proper sequence
        Parameters:
        copy - Array into which the elements of the queue are to be stored.
        Returns:
        array containing all of the elements in this list in proper sequence
